summary:
The “needle” was a race condition in app/counter.js: the counter was incremented with a read-modify-write sequence that lost updates under concurrency.  

Fix applied: replaced the manual sequence with Redis’ atomic INCR command.

Key change in app/counter.js:

```js
async function incrementCounter() {
  const client = createClient();
  const newValue = await client.incr(COUNTER_KEY); // atomic increment
  logger.debug(`Counter incremented -> ${newValue}`);
  return newValue;
}
```

Running ./test.sh now reports:

PASS: Counter is correct
